This paper focuses on the impact of language on requirements engineering, which is a subfield of software engineering (cs.SE). The study involves analyzing the readability of requirements, which involves natural language processing (cs.CL). The experiment also involves human participants, which falls under human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The study uses statistical analysis to compare the effectiveness of different phrasing, which falls under machine learning (cs.LG) and data analysis (cs.CY).
